race.description: Pipe Pro Directional Drilling Maiden Plate
race.comment: Keen to give LONSTAR (5) another chance here. Only start to date was in a much tougher race than this and he had obvious issues there, failing to finish. The jumpouts this time in suggest he's an improved product this time around and he should get his chance from the draw. STERNIN (14) was well in commission last start over 1100m at Kerang when third, beaten 3 lengths. Will find this assignment a little tougher but a bold showing is expected. VILLA CAPITALISTA (16) finished fifth at both runs of the debut prep, when in the market, but had excuses both times and has been trialling well. SMOKE CREEK (13) resumes. Well beaten on racedays to date but has placed in each of her trials so far this campaign.
